WEBVTT

00:02.698 --> 00:04.917
THIS STATION'S FIRST AVENUE.
FIRST AVENUE.

00:04.961 --> 00:07.224
[door chimes]

00:11.359 --> 00:12.925
WHOA. N--UM--

00:12.969 --> 00:13.926
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

00:13.970 --> 00:15.798
OKAY.

00:15.841 --> 00:17.060
DAMN IT.

00:17.104 --> 00:18.148
HEY, MAN, YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO LET COMMUTERS

00:18.192 --> 00:19.584
GET OFF THE TRAIN
BEFORE YOU GET ON

00:19.628 --> 00:21.195
WITH YOUR GIANT
WEIRD BOXES.

00:21.238 --> 00:22.935
SORRY. YOU LOOKED LIKE YOU WERE
READING YOUR TRASHY MAGAZINE.

00:22.979 --> 00:24.763
SUE ME FOR TRYING
TO GET TO A PLACE

00:24.807 --> 00:26.417
BUT ALSO WANTING TO FIND OUT
IF ELIN NORDEGREN

00:26.461 --> 00:27.549
IS MOVING ON WITH HER LIFE.

00:27.592 --> 00:29.116
BY THE WAY,
SHE'S OPEN TO DATING.

00:29.159 --> 00:30.334
YEAH, SO YOU'LL GET OFF
AT THE NEXT STOP.

00:30.378 --> 00:32.075
YEAH, IN BROOKLYN,
WHERE EVERYONE IS

00:32.119 --> 00:34.077
INCREDIBLY INTIMIDATING
AND EXPRESSIVE.

00:34.121 --> 00:35.383
SO THANKS FOR ADDING
THAT TO MY DAY.

00:35.426 --> 00:37.080
AND BY THE WAY,
WHAT'S IN THESE?

00:37.124 --> 00:38.168
LIKE, DEAD BODIES?

00:38.212 --> 00:39.952
STUFFED ANIMALS
FILLED WITH COCAINE?

00:39.996 --> 00:42.259
BABY STROLLERS FOR HAITI,
OKAY?

00:42.303 --> 00:44.435
THEY'VE GOT ALL-TERRAIN
WHEELS ON THEM

00:44.479 --> 00:45.784
SO THAT MALNOURISHED MOTHERS

00:45.828 --> 00:47.395
CAN PUSH THE STROLLERS
THROUGH THE RUBBLE.

00:47.438 --> 00:48.831
[women]
AW.

00:48.874 --> 00:50.789
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT YOU WERE
SOME KIND OF DO-GOODER.

00:50.833 --> 00:52.095
I DO WHAT I DO, ALL RIGHT?

00:52.139 --> 00:53.923
IF OTHER PEOPLE
WANT TO THINK IT'S GOOD,

00:53.966 --> 00:55.055
IT'S ON THEM.

00:55.098 --> 00:56.012
[women]
AW.

00:56.056 --> 00:58.319
OKAY.
ENOUGH, OKAY?

00:58.362 --> 01:00.103
HE'S NOT THE ONLY GOOD PERSON
ON THE SUBWAY.

01:00.147 --> 01:01.191
I'M A DOCTOR.

01:01.235 --> 01:02.149
BUT YOU KNOW THE WAY
YOU WERE DRESSED,

01:02.192 --> 01:03.150
I THOUGHT YOU WERE, LIKE,

01:03.193 --> 01:04.934
A RAPPER'S PUBLICIST
OR SOMETHING.

01:04.977 --> 01:05.891
THANK YOU.

01:05.935 --> 01:07.110
NOT A COMPLIMENT.

01:07.154 --> 01:08.416
LET'S SEE YOUR CARD.

01:08.459 --> 01:10.070
OH, I GET IT.
BECAUSE YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME.

01:10.113 --> 01:12.028
YOU'RE GONNA LOOK
SO DUMB, MISTER.

01:12.072 --> 01:13.029
ALL RIGHT.

01:13.073 --> 01:14.987
"DR. MINDY LAHIRI."

01:15.031 --> 01:16.076
MM-HMM.

01:16.119 --> 01:17.294
CUTE CARD.THANK YOU.

01:17.338 --> 01:19.644
CUTER DOCTOR.WHOA.

01:19.688 --> 01:21.820
WHAT IS HAPPENING HERE?

01:21.864 --> 01:23.083
CAN I CALL YOU?

01:23.126 --> 01:26.216
FOR WHAT, LIKE A DATE
OR SOMETHING WEIRD?

01:26.260 --> 01:28.436
FOR A DATE.[door chimes]

01:28.479 --> 01:31.003
WE'LL SEE IF IT TURNS INTO
SOMETHING WEIRD, OKAY?

01:31.047 --> 01:33.310
THAT'S A VERY
SEXY THING TO SAY.

01:33.354 --> 01:35.095
IF OTHER PEOPLE WANNA
THINK THAT'S SEXY,

01:35.138 --> 01:36.705
THAT'S ON THEM.

01:36.748 --> 01:37.836
THIS IS YOUR STOP.

01:37.880 --> 01:40.535
YEAH, I SHOULD GO.
OKAY, YEAH.

01:40.578 --> 01:43.146
OH, GOD,
WHAT IS THIS, A BAND?

01:43.190 --> 01:44.234
OKAY, SIR,
PUT A SHIRT ON.

01:44.278 --> 01:46.323
RABBI, I HAVE
TO GET BY.

01:46.367 --> 01:49.021
THERE'S A SITU--OKAY.
WHAT A HORRIBLE SNAKE.

01:49.065 --> 01:51.763
STUPID BROOKLYN.

01:51.807 --> 01:54.766
[upbeat music]

01:54.810 --> 02:02.905
â™ª

02:06.169 --> 02:08.824
GUYS, I MET A HOT STRANGER
ON THE SUBWAY,

02:08.867 --> 02:10.608
AND HE DID NOT TRY
TO KILL ME.

02:10.652 --> 02:12.741
IN FACT, HE WAS HANDSOME.
AND GET THIS--

02:12.784 --> 02:14.830
HE WAS SENDING BOXES
TO HAITI.

02:14.873 --> 02:16.919
OKAY, I UNDERSTAND THAT BOXES
ARE FUN TO PLAY IN,

02:16.962 --> 02:19.226
BUT PEOPLE IN HAITI
NEED SUPPLIES.

02:19.269 --> 02:21.053
SOUNDS BETTER THAN
YOUR LAST COUPLE GUYS.

02:21.097 --> 02:22.533
I GUESS THAT WE'LL JUST WAIT
FOR THE OTHER SHOE TO DROP.

02:22.577 --> 02:24.666
DARK-SECRET-WISE.

02:24.709 --> 02:26.058
OKAY, MR. CYNICAL.

02:26.102 --> 02:28.104
I FEEL SORRY FOR YOU
THAT YOU CAN'T BELIEVE

02:28.148 --> 02:30.411
A PERSON EXISTS WHO DOES
GOOD FOR OTHER PEOPLE.

02:30.454 --> 02:33.065
HEY, I'M GOING TO THE PRACTICE
VOLUNTEER TRIP NEXT WEEK.

02:33.109 --> 02:34.458
IN FACT, MINDY,
YOU'RE THE ONLY PERSON

02:34.502 --> 02:36.199
WHO CURRENTLY ISN'T GOING.

02:36.243 --> 02:39.071
UGH. A WOMEN'S PRISON?
YOU GUYS, COME ON.

02:39.115 --> 02:40.334
IF I WANTED TO GET SHANKED,

02:40.377 --> 02:42.162
I'D JUST SHAVE MY LEGS
DRUNK AGAIN--AM I RIGHT?

02:42.205 --> 02:45.034
MINDY, THE AMERICAN PRISON
SYSTEM IS A BLEMISH

02:45.077 --> 02:46.992
ON AN OTHERWISE
BEAUTIFUL COUNTRY.

02:47.036 --> 02:48.559
THE LEAST WE CAN DO
IS OFFER

02:48.603 --> 02:50.082
THESE POOR SOULS
FREE HEALTH CARE.

02:50.126 --> 02:52.259
I AM CHIPPING IN
FOR THE VAN, AM I NOT?

02:52.302 --> 02:54.870
AND THAT IS A VERY
GENEROUS CONTRIBUTION.

02:54.913 --> 02:56.437
THIS IS LIKE
HABITAT FOR HUMANITY.

02:56.480 --> 02:57.960
WOULD YOU PREFER SOMEONE
WHO HAS NEVER

02:58.003 --> 02:59.179
PICKED UP A HAMMER BEFORE,

02:59.222 --> 03:00.223
OR WOULD YOU PREFER A CHECK

03:00.267 --> 03:02.791
TO BUY AS MANY HAMMERS
AS YOU WANT?

03:02.834 --> 03:04.358
SO NO ONE IS HAMMERING
IN YOUR SCENARIO.

03:04.401 --> 03:06.360
MINDY, THESE INMATES,
THEY NEED OUR HELP.

03:06.403 --> 03:07.839
THEY'RE MOSTLY GOOD PEOPLE.

03:07.883 --> 03:09.232
THAT IS TRUE.
THEY MAINLY ARE GOOD PEOPLE.

03:09.276 --> 03:11.147
BUT AS AN EX-CON,
LET ME TELL YOU,

03:11.191 --> 03:14.585
THEY ARE MOSTLY
DEAD-EYED CREEPS AND SAVAGES.

03:14.629 --> 03:15.673
MORGAN MAKES A GREAT POINT.

03:15.717 --> 03:19.155
SEE? YOU ARE
THE TALLEST MAN

03:19.199 --> 03:20.461
THAT I'VE EVER BEEN
ON A DATE WITH.

03:20.504 --> 03:22.245
THANK YOU.
I DATED A GUY ONCE
THAT WAS 5'1".

03:22.289 --> 03:23.986
HE WAS A COCKSWAIN
FOR A CREW TEAM.

03:24.029 --> 03:25.292
I RODE A CREW.
REALLY?

03:25.335 --> 03:26.641
I RODE WITH
THE WINKLEVOSS TWINS.

03:26.684 --> 03:29.121
THEY CALLED US
THE WINKLEVOSS TRIPLETS.

03:29.165 --> 03:30.601
THIS IS A REALLY NICE DATE.

03:30.645 --> 03:33.125
YOU KNOW, THIS PLACE
USED TO BE A SPEAKEASY.REALLY?

03:33.169 --> 03:35.215
UH-HUH, BABE RUTH
WAS SAID TO HAVE THROWN UP

03:35.258 --> 03:36.477
AT THAT BOOTH
OVER THERE.

03:36.520 --> 03:38.130
THAT'S FUNNY THAT YOU
BRING UP BABE RUTH,

03:38.174 --> 03:40.263
BECAUSE I SAW DEREK JETER
AT A NIGHT CLUB ONE NIGHT.WHOA.

03:40.307 --> 03:41.656
I THINK IT WAS DEREK JETER.

03:41.699 --> 03:43.658
HE WAS DEFINITELY MIXED RACE.GOOD ENOUGH FOR ME.

03:43.701 --> 03:45.181
I LOVE NEW YORK CITY.

03:45.225 --> 03:46.878
EVERY BUILDING
USED TO BE SOMETHING ELSE.

03:46.922 --> 03:49.185
FOR INSTANCE, MY APARTMENT USED
TO BE A TUBERCULOSIS HOSPITAL.

03:49.229 --> 03:50.186
ARE YOU KIDDING?

03:50.230 --> 03:51.579
MYAPARTMENT BUILDING

03:51.622 --> 03:54.016
USED TO BE
A TUBERCULOSIS HOSPITAL.

03:54.059 --> 03:56.975
I FEEL LIKE THERE SHOULD
BE A WALKING TOUR

03:57.019 --> 03:59.021
OF ALL THE POCKETS
IN NEW YORK CITY...
TOTALLY.

03:59.064 --> 04:00.370
WHERE ILLNESSES
HAVE RAVAGED THE POPULATION.

04:00.414 --> 04:01.589
YES.
DO YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

04:01.632 --> 04:03.373
LIKE, UPPER WESTSIDE
IS SMALLPOX.
MM-HMM.

04:03.417 --> 04:06.376
ROOSEVELT ISLAND IS POLIO,
IRONICALLY ENOUGH.

04:06.420 --> 04:07.421
WE'RE GOING ON THIS TOUR.

04:07.464 --> 04:08.683
[waiter]
HERE'S YOUR APPETIZER.

04:08.726 --> 04:10.902
THANKS.
OH, MY GOD,
THIS LOOKS SO GOOD.

04:10.946 --> 04:12.295
CASEY, YOU'VE GOT
TO TRY THIS.
LORD JESUS,

04:12.339 --> 04:13.905
WE ARE YOUR BROTHERS
AND SISTERS,

04:13.949 --> 04:15.298
AND WE GATHER HERE
IN YOUR NAME,
[mouth full]
OH, MY GOD.

04:15.342 --> 04:16.778
IN YOUR LOVE.

04:16.821 --> 04:19.302
GIVE US YOUR BLESSING
AND BLESS THIS FOOD FOR US.

04:19.346 --> 04:22.784
AMEN.
ALL RIGHT, LET'S DO THIS.

04:22.827 --> 04:24.046
OH, IS IT FUNKY?

04:24.089 --> 04:25.308
DID WE GET SOME
FUNKY BRUSCHETTA?

04:25.352 --> 04:26.440
WERE YOU JUST PRAYING?

04:26.483 --> 04:27.615
WAS THAT WEIRD FOR YOU?

04:27.658 --> 04:29.051
NO. DO YOU DO THAT A LOT?

04:29.094 --> 04:30.531
I DO. YEAH.

04:30.574 --> 04:31.532
IT'S KIND OF LIKE

04:31.575 --> 04:32.968
AN OCCUPATIONAL HAZARD,
I GUESS.

04:33.011 --> 04:35.100
I'M A MINISTER, SO--
HA HA HA!

04:35.144 --> 04:36.101
NO, I AM.

04:36.145 --> 04:37.451
OH, YOU WERE NOT KIDDING?

04:39.279 --> 04:40.671
DANNY, DO YOU
REMEMBER THAT GUY

04:40.715 --> 04:42.107
THAT I SAID
I WAS GOING OUT WITH?

04:42.151 --> 04:43.326
VAGUELY.
GET THIS.

04:43.370 --> 04:45.241
HE'S A PRIEST.A CATHOLIC PRIEST?

04:45.285 --> 04:47.025
YOU SHOULD FEEL WEIRD,
BECAUSE YOU'RE GOING TO HELL.

04:47.069 --> 04:48.200
NO, HE'S LUTHERAN.

04:48.244 --> 04:49.201
WELL, THAT JUST MAKES HIM
A MINISTER.

04:49.245 --> 04:50.377
AND YOU'RE MISSING
THE POINT.

04:50.420 --> 04:52.988
WHEN DINNER CAME,
HE BEGAN TO PRAY.

04:53.031 --> 04:54.381
AT A RESTAURANT, DANNY.

04:54.424 --> 04:55.643
OKAY, WHOA.
HOLD--HOLD IT RIGHT THERE.

04:55.686 --> 04:57.035
BEFORE YOU SAY ANYTHING
OFFENSIVE,

04:57.079 --> 05:00.387
LET ME TELL YOU THAT
I'M A PRETTY SERIOUS CATHOLIC.

05:00.430 --> 05:01.692
REALLY?

05:01.736 --> 05:03.346
HOW CAN SOMEONE WITH
A GOD COMPLEX BE RELIGIOUS?

05:03.390 --> 05:04.695
AREN'T YOU AFRAID
OF BEING SMITED?

05:04.739 --> 05:07.698
NO, I'M NOT ONE OF THOSE
CRAZY FANATIC CATHOLICS.

05:07.742 --> 05:09.004
I JUST--I GO TO CHURCH
EVERY SUNDAY,

05:09.047 --> 05:10.614
FATHER FRANCIS
COMES OVER FOR DINNER

05:10.658 --> 05:12.094
FIVE TIMES A MONTH, MAX.

05:12.137 --> 05:14.357
YOU KNOW WHAT,
YOU ARE PERFECT FOR THIS.

05:14.401 --> 05:17.055
WILL YOU PLEASE COME WITH ME
TO CASEY'S SERVICE THIS WEEKEND?

05:17.099 --> 05:18.927
I KIND OF LIKE HIM,
AND I NEED TO MAKE SURE

05:18.970 --> 05:21.233
THAT HE'S NORMAL AND NOT SOME,
LIKE, WEIRDO CULT LEADER.

05:21.277 --> 05:23.105
YOU KNOW WHAT?
SURE.

05:23.148 --> 05:24.324
REALLY?YEAH.

05:24.367 --> 05:25.890
I ACTUALLY FIND
THAT CONFRONTING

05:25.934 --> 05:27.414
OTHER FAITHS
STRENGTHENS MINE.

05:27.457 --> 05:29.459
I ONCE FASTED FOR A MONTH
DURING RAMADAN

05:29.503 --> 05:31.374
JUST TO BE MORE CATHOLIC.OKAY.

05:31.418 --> 05:32.854
YOU KNOW, I'VE WANDERED
INTO BRISES, AND I COME OUT,

05:32.897 --> 05:34.725
AND I'M MORE CATHOLIC,
SO I DO THIS STUFF--

05:34.769 --> 05:35.857
YOU CAN HEAD OUT
BECAUSE I'M GONNA FINISH.

05:35.900 --> 05:37.728
OKAY, GREAT.
SO SUNDAY.

05:37.772 --> 05:38.903
SEE YOU SUNDAY.I'LL HELP YOU OUT.

05:38.947 --> 05:41.253
THANKS, DANNY.GREAT. NO PROBLEM.

05:41.297 --> 05:42.951
[Rishi]
SO SHOULD I BE WORRIED

05:42.994 --> 05:44.126
THAT YOU'RE GOING TO CHURCH?

05:44.169 --> 05:45.649
HEY, RISHI,
I DIDN'T ASK YOU

05:45.693 --> 05:47.259
TO SPEND SPRING BREAK
ON MY COUCH, OKAY?

05:47.303 --> 05:48.609
I DON'T NEED YOUR JUDGMENT.

05:48.652 --> 05:49.958
ALL RIGHT, WELL, GIVE ME
SOME OF THAT DOCTOR MONEY,

05:50.001 --> 05:51.394
AND I'LL BE
IN MEXICO TOMORROW.

05:51.438 --> 05:53.004
WITH YOUR HEAD
CHOPPED OFF, RISHI?

05:53.048 --> 05:55.006
I DON'T THINK SO.
I HAVE A CD OF OCEAN SOUNDS.

05:55.050 --> 05:56.834
I HAVE MARGARITA MIX.
YOU ARE FINE HERE.

05:56.878 --> 05:58.227
[Rishi] LOOK, WOMAN.

05:58.270 --> 06:01.012
JUST DON'T CHANGE YOURSELF
FOR THIS GUY, ALL RIGHT?

06:01.056 --> 06:02.710
I MEAN, I DIG IT
WHEN GIRLS DO IT FOR ME,

06:02.753 --> 06:04.102
BUT THEN I TOTALLY
LOSE RESPECT FOR THEM.

06:04.146 --> 06:05.713
[Mindy]
EW, RISHI.

06:05.756 --> 06:07.497
THERE IS NO WAY THAT
I'M GONNA CHANGE WHO I AM.

06:10.326 --> 06:11.371
WHAT ARE YOU WEARING?

06:11.414 --> 06:12.546
CHURCH CLOTHES.

06:12.589 --> 06:14.286
HAVE YOU NEVER SEEN
A TYLER PERRY MOVIE?

06:16.201 --> 06:19.161
[organ music]

06:19.204 --> 06:25.428
â™ª

06:25.472 --> 06:26.908
[man]
OH, ARE YOU KIDDING?

06:26.951 --> 06:28.692
[second man] YEAH, SERIOUSLY.

06:28.736 --> 06:29.998
YOU GOTTA LOSE THE HAT.

06:30.041 --> 06:31.303
DANNY, IT'S PART
OF MY OUTFIT.

06:31.347 --> 06:32.435
JUST LOSE THE HAT.

06:32.479 --> 06:34.306
LOSE YOUR TIE.
IT'S FOR MY LOOK.

06:34.350 --> 06:36.047
IT'S JUST--PEOPLE WILL
THINK IT'S WEIRD IF I DON'T--

06:36.091 --> 06:37.309
[whispering]
I CAN'T SEE.
OH.

06:37.353 --> 06:38.659
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

06:38.702 --> 06:40.443
SORRY.JUST KEEP YOUR PANTS ON.
IT'S FINE.

06:40.487 --> 06:43.011
KEEP IT DOWN IN HERE, OKAY?DID IT MESS UP MY HAIR?

06:43.054 --> 06:44.012
[whispering]
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

06:44.055 --> 06:45.492
GOD DOESN'T JUDGE.

06:45.535 --> 06:47.494
I WANT CASEY TO LIKE IT.
I DON'T CARE ABOUT GOD.

06:47.537 --> 06:49.278
CAN YOU SAY THAT
ANY LOUDER?

06:49.321 --> 06:51.280
[Danny]
OKAY, HERE WE GO.

06:51.323 --> 06:54.283
[pulsing techno music]

06:54.326 --> 06:57.591
â™ª

06:57.634 --> 06:59.201
WHAT IS THAT HEADPHONES GUY
DOING?

06:59.244 --> 07:01.421
OH, MY GOD.HE'S RUINING THE RECORD.

07:01.464 --> 07:02.596
[Mindy]
DANNY, THAT'S MOBY. WHO?

07:02.639 --> 07:03.988
[Mindy]
THE MUSICIAN.

07:04.032 --> 07:05.381
THIS IS THE COOLEST PARTY
I'VE EVER GONE TO.

07:05.425 --> 07:06.382
IT'S NOT A PARTY.

07:06.426 --> 07:07.383
MOBY.

07:07.427 --> 07:13.084
[cheers and applause]

07:13.128 --> 07:15.260
COME ON.

07:15.304 --> 07:17.001
THIS IS GREAT.

07:17.045 --> 07:19.221
I LOVE EACH AND EVERY
ONE OF YOU. THANK YOU.

07:19.264 --> 07:21.528
I'M EXCITED FOR TODAY.
I'VE GOT A BIG ANNOUNCEMENT.

07:21.571 --> 07:22.920
I HOPE THIS IS NOT ABOUT ME.

07:22.964 --> 07:24.487
I WILL BE SO EMBARRASSED.

07:24.531 --> 07:25.967
I HATE GOD.

07:26.010 --> 07:26.968
[all gasping]

07:27.011 --> 07:29.100
OH, MAN.
WE'RE ALL DEAD.

07:29.144 --> 07:30.101
[Casey]
AND HERE'S WHY.

07:30.145 --> 07:31.189
HAD A LONG DAY AT THE OFFICE.

07:31.233 --> 07:33.191
GOT HOME, I WAS EXHAUSTED.

07:33.235 --> 07:35.150
YOU KNOW, I KICK OFF
MY DRESS SHOES, PUT ON MY UGGS.

07:35.193 --> 07:37.239
THANK YOU, MOBY.
APPRECIATE THOSE.

07:37.282 --> 07:38.588
WHAT I WANT TO DO--

07:38.632 --> 07:41.156
WATCH A LITTLE GAME OF THRONES
ON THE DVR.

07:41.199 --> 07:43.027
TURNS OUT--WASN'T RECORDED.

07:43.071 --> 07:44.464
I LOOK UP AT THE BIG MAN,
I GO,

07:44.507 --> 07:46.030
"WHAT'S UP WITH THAT, G?"

07:46.074 --> 07:48.032
THAT'S WHY I HATE GOD.

07:48.076 --> 07:49.730
AND I WANT EVERYONE HERE
TO SAY IT WITH ME.

07:49.773 --> 07:51.035
I HATE GOD?

07:51.079 --> 07:52.602
SHE HATES GOD.
WHO ELSE HATES GOD?

07:52.646 --> 07:54.212
[all]
I HATE GOD!

07:54.256 --> 07:55.779
NO, NO, NO, NO.
I'M NOT ON BOARD WITH THIS.

07:55.823 --> 07:56.824
I HATE GOD.

07:56.867 --> 07:58.434
[all]
I HATE GOD.

07:58.478 --> 08:00.001
OKAY. OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

08:00.044 --> 08:02.482
WE ALL HATE GOD,
AND HE HEARS YOUR ANGER.

08:02.525 --> 08:03.526
YOU KNOW WHAT?

08:03.570 --> 08:06.398
GOD STILL LOVES YOU ANYWAY.

08:06.442 --> 08:08.226
[murmuring] OH, YES, YES!

08:08.270 --> 08:09.445
THAT WAS AMAZING.

08:09.489 --> 08:10.577
[woman]
AMEN.

08:10.620 --> 08:12.100
SOMETHING'S BEEN
BUGGING ME TODAY.

08:12.143 --> 08:14.581
NOW HE'S TALKING ABOUT YOU.SHH.

08:14.624 --> 08:15.930
I SEE A BUNCH
OF WEEKEND WARRIORS.

08:15.973 --> 08:17.584
I'M NOT SEEING YOU GUYS
HERE DURING THE WEEK.

08:17.627 --> 08:20.282
GUYS, GOD IS WITH YOU
24/7.

08:20.325 --> 08:22.458
EVEN WHEN YOU'RE DOING
YOU KNOW WHAT.

08:22.502 --> 08:24.808
I'M NOT TELLING YOU
TO BE SOME RELIGIOUS FREAK.

08:24.852 --> 08:27.594
IF I WANT TO GO TO BONNAROO
AND SEE THE BLACK KEYS,

08:27.637 --> 08:28.812
IT DOESN'T MEAN
I WANT TO GO TO HELL.

08:28.856 --> 08:29.944
I JUST WANT TO ROCK!

08:29.987 --> 08:31.598
LET GOD IN.
HE'S COOL.

08:31.641 --> 08:34.078
IT'S ACTUALLY KIND OF
LIKE BRUNO MARS SINGS.

08:34.122 --> 08:38.169
â™ª I NEVER HAD MUCH FAITH
IN LOVE â™ª

08:38.213 --> 08:40.215
â™ª OR MIRACLES

08:40.258 --> 08:43.044
â™ª NEVER BEEN ONE TO PUT

08:43.087 --> 08:46.177
â™ª MY HEART ON THE LINE

08:46.221 --> 08:48.005
[music amps up]

08:48.049 --> 08:49.572
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

08:49.616 --> 08:54.577
â™ª BUT SWIMMING IN YOUR WATER'S
SOMETHING SPIRIT-U-AL â™ª

08:54.621 --> 08:56.579
